136
00:06:41.842 --> 00:06:43.301
<i>[Keiji] Delicious!</i>

137
00:06:43.302 --> 00:06:46.137
<i>The savory aroma and the
perfect amount of bitterness.</i>

138
00:06:46.138 --> 00:06:48.640
<i>Nothing like stink
bugs for breakfast.</i>

139
00:06:48.641 --> 00:06:50.475
<i>And on top of that.</i>

140
00:06:50.476 --> 00:06:52.185
<i>they're great for digestion</i>

141
00:06:52.186 --> 00:06:55.355
<i>and well known to promote
healthy bowel movements.</i>

142
00:06:55.356 --> 00:06:57.607
(Keiji grunts)

143
00:06:57.608 --> 00:06:59.692
<i>Delicious and nutritious.</i>

144
00:06:59.693 --> 00:07:03.113
<i>Truly an example of killing
two birds with one stone!</i>

145
00:07:05.199 --> 00:07:10.204
- (children playing)
- (water sloshing)

146
00:07:16.043 --> 00:07:18.878
[Girls] Look. a chicken!

147
00:07:18.879 --> 00:07:20.463
His crown is just adorable!

148
00:07:20.464 --> 00:07:22.090
What's a chicken doing here?

149
00:07:22.091 --> 00:07:23.257
[Girl] Where did you come from?

150
00:07:23.258 --> 00:07:24.258
[Girl] Are you from the zoo?

151
00:07:24.259 --> 00:07:25.218
[Girl] Maybe he flew the coop!

152
00:07:25.219 --> 00:07:26.928
<i>[Keiji] I hate little kids.</i>

153
00:07:26.929 --> 00:07:29.764
<i>The brats are always
rude. stubborn and loud.</i>

154
00:07:29.765 --> 00:07:31.057
[Girl] Hey. are you hungry?

155
00:07:31.058 --> 00:07:32.058
You want some of this?

156
00:07:32.059 --> 00:07:32.893
Koke!

157
00:07:33.727 --> 00:07:35.520
It's yummy fried chicken!

158
00:07:35.521 --> 00:07:37.188
You're gonna love it!

159
00:07:37.189 --> 00:07:39.065
Koke? <i>Fried what?</i>

160
00:07:39.066 --> 00:07:41.067
<i>Is she for real?</i>

161
00:07:41.068 --> 00:07:42.485
(Keiji gagging)

162
00:07:42.486 --> 00:07:43.736
Ooh!

163
00:07:43.737 --> 00:07:45.238
We're gonna have lotsa
fun with this guy!

164
00:07:45.239 --> 00:07:47.490
You let that poor thing
go. you're hurting him!

165
00:07:47.491 --> 00:07:48.324
Huh?

166
00:07:48.325 --> 00:07:49.576
Shut up. dumb brat!

167
00:07:50.703 --> 00:07:52.662
Let's go. Come on!

168
00:07:52.663 --> 00:07:54.247
[Hiroshi] Whoa. his
comb is really cool.

169
00:07:54.248 --> 00:07:55.832
You guys are a
bunch of brats. too!

170
00:07:55.833 --> 00:07:57.251
Yeah. that's right!

171
00:07:59.503 --> 00:08:01.004
What should we do with him?

172
00:08:01.005 --> 00:08:02.547
Let's eat him for lunch!

173
00:08:02.548 --> 00:08:04.757
You idiot. what if he's got
some weird chicken disease?

174
00:08:04.758 --> 00:08:05.883
Oh. right.

175
00:08:05.884 --> 00:08:06.968
[Brown Haired Boy]
I got an idea!

176
00:08:06.969 --> 00:08:08.803
How about we feed him to my cat?

177
00:08:08.804 --> 00:08:10.555
[Hiroshi] That'll be awesome!

178
00:08:10.556 --> 00:08:12.724
- (both chuckles)
- Koke!

179
00:08:12.725 --> 00:08:13.975
Hey. get back here!

180
00:08:13.976 --> 00:08:16.061
- [Hiroshi] Whoa!
- Stop trying to get away!

181
00:08:17.688 --> 00:08:20.274
<i>Don't waste my time.
you little punks!</i>

182
00:08:21.191 --> 00:08:22.900
Kokokokoko!

183
00:08:22.901 --> 00:08:25.070
Give it up. you damn chicken!

184
00:08:26.864 --> 00:08:28.281
<i>They just won't quit!</i>

185
00:08:28.282 --> 00:08:29.700
Kokokokoko. koke!

186
00:08:35.372 --> 00:08:37.206
[Brown Haired Boy]
Hold it right there!

187
00:08:37.207 --> 00:08:38.374
Huh?

188
00:08:38.375 --> 00:08:39.460
Kokokokoko!

189
00:08:42.212 --> 00:08:43.713
Koke-ko.

190
00:08:43.714 --> 00:08:44.548
Oh.

191
00:08:47.009 --> 00:08:51.262
- Koko!
- (boys panting)

192
00:08:51.263 --> 00:08:52.597
What's going on?

193
00:08:52.598 --> 00:08:55.308
That's our rooster.
we're taking him back.

194
00:08:55.309 --> 00:08:56.185
Oh?

195
00:08:58.103 --> 00:08:58.896
Koko.

196
00:09:00.481 --> 00:09:02.774
I think you may be confused.

197
00:09:02.775 --> 00:09:04.984
This rooster lives here with me.

198
00:09:04.985 --> 00:09:06.069
[Both] Huh?

199
00:09:06.070 --> 00:09:07.737
Now. Mr. Cluckers!

200
00:09:07.738 --> 00:09:10.490
How many times have I told
you not to leave the yard?

201
00:09:10.491 --> 00:09:12.659
<i>[Keiji] Mr. Cluckers?</i>

202
00:09:12.660 --> 00:09:13.618
Forgive us.

203
00:09:13.619 --> 00:09:15.662
We'll try to do better.

204
00:09:15.663 --> 00:09:18.331
(both grunting)

205
00:09:18.332 --> 00:09:19.916
Tsk! Let's get out of here!

206
00:09:19.917 --> 00:09:20.917
Yeah.

207
00:09:20.918 --> 00:09:21.752
Koke.

208
00:09:23.170 --> 00:09:25.088
(old man chuckles)

209
00:09:25.089 --> 00:09:27.716
<i>You saved my feathers. Old Man.</i>

210
00:09:31.720 --> 00:09:35.056
Do you really think
that rooster is his?

211
00:09:35.057 --> 00:09:37.225
No way that bird belongs
to the old geezer.

212
00:09:37.226 --> 00:09:38.476
- he lied to us!
- My quota.

213
00:09:38.477 --> 00:09:39.311
My quota.

214
00:09:40.938 --> 00:09:41.981
I must reach it.

215
00:09:42.940 --> 00:09:44.440
Yes. sir.

216
00:09:44.441 --> 00:09:46.025
This month. yes.

217
00:09:46.026 --> 00:09:46.860
My quota.

218
00:09:48.279 --> 00:09:50.822
<i>Thanks for taking
care of me. Old Man.</i>

219
00:09:50.823 --> 00:09:54.325
<i>But I've got things to
do and places to go.</i>

220
00:09:54.326 --> 00:09:55.827
Koke.

221
00:09:55.828 --> 00:09:57.036
Sorry to say.

222
00:09:57.037 --> 00:09:58.956
This is all I have to offer you.

223
00:10:00.374 --> 00:10:03.042
<i>[Keiji] Brown rice.
corn and shiso leaves.</i>

224
00:10:03.043 --> 00:10:04.169
<i>You know what this is?</i>

225
00:10:05.504 --> 00:10:09.590
<i>This is undeniably a
special and bountiful feast!</i>

226
00:10:09.591 --> 00:10:10.758
(Keiji aggressively pecking)

227
00:10:10.759 --> 00:10:11.926
It's that good?

228
00:10:11.927 --> 00:10:13.928
I'm glad you're enjoying it.

229
00:10:13.929 --> 00:10:16.723
(Keiji aggressively pecking)

230
00:10:16.724 --> 00:10:17.558
Ah.

231
00:10:18.851 --> 00:10:19.685
Koke?

232
00:10:21.353 --> 00:10:24.063
I remember how my wife
would feed the sparrows

233
00:10:24.064 --> 00:10:25.649
that would come to visit us.

234
00:10:28.485 --> 00:10:29.737
I think of her often.

235
00:10:30.988 --> 00:10:33.406
I really wish I
had retired sooner.

236
00:10:33.407 --> 00:10:34.741
If I had stopped teaching.

237
00:10:34.742 --> 00:10:36.577
I could have spent
more time with her.

238
00:10:38.245 --> 00:10:40.913
{\an8}<i>♪ I'll be walking alone ♪</i>

239
00:10:40.914 --> 00:10:43.916
{\an8}<i>♪ For lonely long time ♪</i>

240
00:10:43.917 --> 00:10:45.335
<i>[Old Woman] No need to fight!</i>

241
00:10:45.336 --> 00:10:46.586
<i>There's enough for everyone.</i>

242
00:10:46.587 --> 00:10:47.754
<i>There.</i>

243
00:10:47.755 --> 00:10:49.506
<i>Don't eat too fast.
now. (chuckles).</i>

244
00:10:52.885 --> 00:10:55.053
{\an8}<i>♪ Searching for the answers ♪</i>

245
00:10:55.054 --> 00:10:59.391
{\an8}<i>♪ But where am I
supposed to go ohh ♪</i>

246
00:11:01.226 --> 00:11:04.020
And here I am.
talking your ear off.

247
00:11:04.021 --> 00:11:06.230
Somehow I feel
comfortable with you

248
00:11:06.231 --> 00:11:07.858
like I could tell you anything.

249
00:11:09.193 --> 00:11:12.028
<i>[Keiji] I understand what
you're saying. Old Man.</i>

250
00:11:12.029 --> 00:11:14.782
<i>I should've spent more
time with her as well.</i>

251
00:11:15.866 --> 00:11:17.784
